-- Chilean Stocks: Cervecerias Unidas, CFR Pharmaceuticals, Ripley
-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 2012-04-05T17:14:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-05/chilean-stocks-banco-santander-besalco-and-cfr-pharmaceuticals.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close.  The  Ipsa index  rose 0.3 percent to 4,647.99. The  MSCI Chile
index (MXCL)  gained 0.4 percent to 2,663.77.  Cia Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU)  (CCU CC) fell 1.9 percent to
7,192.2 pesos. The country’s largest brewer has lost 3.9 percent
in the two days since being cut to hold from buy at Deutsche
Bank AG.  CFR Pharmaceuticals SA (CFR)  (CFR CC) rose 2.1 percent to 124.01
pesos. The  drug company  agreed to buy 50 percent of  India ’s
Stellence Pharmscience Private Ltd. for $20.8 million, said a
regulatory filing released after the close of trading yesterday.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)  (RIPLEY CC) climbed 2.5 percent to 566.39
pesos. Chile’s third-largest department-store operator led gains
by interest-rate sensitive stocks after annual inflation
unexpectedly slowed back to within the central bank’s target
range, easing pressure on policy makers to raise borrowing
costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
